cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes an extended deep reinforcement learning method that uses a generative model to reduce the number of training trials required for real-world tasks. The paper uses a deep q-network method as the deep reinforcement learning method and a deep auto-encoder as the generative model. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, since the paper deals with image processing, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper uses neural networks, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
